This error typically occurs when there is a mismatch between the property name specified in the &quot;mappedBy&quot; attribute of a Hibernate mapping annotation and the actual property name in the target entity.

Here&#39;s an example of how this error might occur:

Suppose you have two entities: &quot;Order&quot; and &quot;OrderLineItem&quot;, and you want to map a one-to-many relationship from Order to OrderLineItem. You might define the mapping on the Order entity as follows:

    @OneToMany(mappedBy=&quot;order&quot;)
    private List&lt;OrderLineItem&gt; lineItems;

In this mapping, the &quot;mappedBy&quot; attribute specifies that the &quot;order&quot; 
property in the OrderLineItem entity is the inverse side of the relationship.

Now suppose that there is a typo in the property name specified in the mappedBy attribute, like this:

    @OneToMany(mappedBy=&quot;orders&quot;)
    private List&lt;OrderLineItem&gt; lineItems;

In this case, Hibernate will not be able to find the &quot;orders&quot; property in the OrderLineItem entity, and it will throw the &quot;mappedBy reference an unknown target entity property&quot; error.

To fix this error, you should double-check that the property name specified in the mappedBy attribute matches the actual property name in the target entity.

